it.slyce.sdk

Interface SlyceSession


  • public interface SlyceSession
    Defines the behavior of a Slyce SDK session. Specifically, the session is used to create and manage Slyce SDK operations (e.g., barcode detection, image match, and visual search).

      • startSearchTask

        SlyceSearchTask startSearchTask(SlyceSearchRequest request,
                                java.lang.String workflowIdOrName,
                                SlyceSearchTaskListener listener)
                         throws SlyceInvalidSessionException
        Creates and starts a search task based on the provided request and workflow identifier.
        Parameters:
        request - The search request.
        workflowIdOrName - The workflow identifier, or workflow name for example, `SlyceWorkflowNames.WORKFLOW_FIND_SIMILAR`.
        listener - A listener to add to the task. Nullable.
        Returns:
        a new `SlyceSearchTask` for the request and workflow identifier.
        Throws:
        SlyceInvalidSessionException - The Slyce session may be closed.

      • createScanner

        SlyceScanner createScanner(android.content.Context context,
                           android.hardware.Camera camera,
                           java.lang.String lensId)
                    throws SlyceLensException,
                           SlyceInvalidSessionException
        Creates a new SlyceScanner matching the spec of the provided lens ID. Note that if the SlyceSession has been closed or the lens ID is not found, null will be returned.
        Parameters:
        camera - The camera.
        context - The context.
        lensId - The lens ID used to configure the SlyceScanner.
        Returns:
        a new SlyceScanner, or null if lens ID not found or session is closed.
        Throws:
        SlyceLensException - if lensID is invalid. LensID could be invalid or not an acceptable lens.
        SlyceInvalidSessionException - The Slyce session may be closed.
